name: Above All
description:
Although a few brave individuals officially started parachuting in 1797, it was the military that developed parachuting technology as a way to save aircrews from emergencies aboard balloons and aircraft in flight, later as a way of delivering soldiers to the battlefield. This chevron inspired logo is the A for Above superimposed by the A for All and it represents our sport's connection to paratroopers.
 
This tee shirt was designed by Miami's own Arnold Steiner. Get to know this designer, visit www.ArnoldSteiner.com

name: OCCUPY THE SKY! (Black)
description:
99% do not have the courage to face the ultimate fear and jump out of a plane, as the 1% that chooses to risk their own lives to fly, WE OCCUPY THE SKY! 

This limited edition tee shirt was designed by Miami's own Cushy Gigs Creative.  Please note that this tee shirt has the Above All logo in the front and 'Occupy the Sky' on the back. It is available in both black and white tee.  Get to know this designer, visit www.CushyGigs.com

Pictured is front side of tee shirt.

name: Swooper Duper
description: "Swooping" is one form of canopy piloting that entails deploying their canopy at 5000 ft, piloting their canopy to an "initiation" point over a swoop course, then turning into a rotating dive dramatically increasing the canopy's speed.  Maximum speeds regularly reach in excess of 90 mph.   Most skydivers sharpen their flying skills in wind tunnels but Swoopers progress only with actual practice. Not only is Swooping a growing activity in the skydiving world, it's the most dangerous.

name: B.A.S.E. Life
description:
B.A.S.E. jumping, is an activity where participants jump from fixed objects and use a parachute to break their fall. B.A.S.E. is an acronym that stands for four categories of fixed objects from which one can jump: buildings, antennas, spans (bridges), and earth (cliffs).

Add some Blunts & Bitches, now you got the lifestyle.
